The fire that razed Kitui county government offices on Sunday last week and destroyed property worth millions of shillings may have been caused by arson, police said. Kitui Central OCPD Muthuri Mwongera to the Star on phone yestertay, although some specimen from the fire had been forwarded to the Government Chemist, there are glaring pointers that the offices were torched. “It is almost overt that the fire was intentional and it was definitely not caused by an electric fault accident. By Tuesday, I will be able to give a comprehensive report after a I get results from the Government Chemist,” Mwongera said.  